She flipped to an empty page and noted the date. Below, she wrote „11.5.648–13.12.648“.
„Do you refresh old memories?“, Ivory inquired and looked at the old notebook. Kari nodded. „Do you think they'll let you out for Christmas? There are only a few days left.“
Kari knocked twice on the lantern. „No“, as Ivory had suspected. The Ice King never let Kari out, as he considered her a „blemish“. She came into the world deaf and was the only daughter of the family, her siblings were all boys.
The same was also true for Ivory. When Ivory came out as non-binary, it seemed as if the world was changing too. As punishment for this peculiarity, Ivory received tasks where one spent most of the time alone.
In addition, Ivory was also forced to serve the princess. However, it didn't make much of a difference to Ivory, as Ivory also gained a friend.
„You're going to have a birthday soon, right?“, asked Ivory, thinking that the princess would be having her birthday in a few days. Kari nodded with a sad flicker in her pale blue eyes.
„Do you want to celebrate your birthday?“, asked Ivory, thinking about the last time the princess answered that question.
„No“, Kari knocked. Ivory knew that this was a difficult topic for her. Her birthday was the day she was locked in this room and her mother was banished. Ivory was a baby at the time, but remembered how upset the servants and the residents of the city were. Ivory had heard that Eirwen was a popular queen. And that she strangely could also predict things that would actually happen.
„Well, what do you want to do?“, asked Ivory. Kari looked at Ivory excitedly. She was holding a piece of paper in her hand. On it was written:
15 x 15 cm canvas
Weiß, various blue tones
Brushes in six different sizes
Easel
„Are you going to get me these things?“, Ivory asked the silent princess, whose braids swung back and forth with her vigorous knocking. „Yes?“ Ivory giggled softly. The otherwise reserved princess showed so much enthusiasm. It was the first time she asked for something that had nothing to do with books and came from outside her room.
„Okay! See you later?“, Ivory asked, stood up, and slithered through the chaos of paper and notebooks.
Kari nodded, turned back to her notes, and wrapped herself in her bed blanket.
Ivory left the room, relieved that the princess finally stepped out of her comfort zone and asked for things outside her reach, like paint colors.
Ivory ran back through the corridors and tried to ignore the whispers of the maids.
“I heard she's possessed by Queen Eirwen and that's why she keeps coming back to this room.”
“I heard she eats children in this room.”
„She looks like a man, that's not normal, is it?“
Ivory held her hands over her ears because she couldn't just ignore the gossip and continued on. The king's painter's room was located in the east wing behind the second door on the left.
Ivory approached the door, which was just as artfully decorated as Kari's door. On it was the White Dragon, one of the six prime dragons that were said to have created Frostfell. For a history-loving painter, the White Dragon on the door made sense.
Ivory opened the door and expected the usual mess. Paint splatters everywhere, brushes and paper scattered all over the room, easels covering every inch of the wall. Unexpectedly, however, a different sight presented itself. The entire room was clean, and in front of a red velvet background stood a chair. On the chair sat Crown Prince Aquilo, who was currently being painted.
„Good morning, Ivory! Do you want to watch how your future king will be painted?“ asked Aquilo and winked at Ivory.
“Excuse me, little prince,” said Ivory, ignoring him for the most part and searched for the things that the silent princess wanted. “I'm only here to get painting supplies.”
“My little girl wants to go already?” asked Aquilo. “I want you to stay instead!”
“I don't want to.” Ivory found the painting supplies on the list and put them in a box. “Besides, I'm not a girl.”
The prince, however, had a different opinion. “Ah sweetie, that's just a phase! As you grow older, you'll grow out of it!” he said unclearly.
“I have to go,” said Ivory and felt uneasy by the prince's answer. On the way, all the ugly remarks that he and others had made about Ivory's gender identity in the past came to mind. I just want to leave here.
“You're leaving already?” The prince suddenly appeared at the door and ignored the loud objections of the royal painter.
“That's not behavior for a future king!” said Ivory.
“No one will find out. People won't believe you and the painter will be silent if his life is worth something.” He glanced briefly at the painter and then leaned in closer to Ivory. “How about a date?” Ivory had been harassed in the past, but never by a prince, and certainly not by the crown prince.
“Do you actually know what the word «No» means?” Ivory said, spitting it out and pushing the crown prince away from her.
“No”, Aquilo replied with a smile. Of course, the crown prince, who can have anything he wants, doesn't know what the word „No“ means.
Ivory rolled her eyes. "Why on earth do you want to go out with someone like me? You must have at least 100 admirers!"
"Actually, it's 50," interrupted Aquilo, still smiling. He threw his hair back, which whirled around in the cold air.
"Now, can you get it? Why exactly me? I'm a danger to the palace." Ivory crossed her arms.
"You're the most beautiful girl I've ever seen." Aquilo lifted Ivory's chin with his finger and forced Ivory to look at him.
